      "title": "Planning versus speed: an experimental examination of what Planned Codes of the Cognitive Assessment System measures",
      "abstract": "Abstract This study provided validity evidence that the Cognitive Assessment System, Planned Codes subtest measures planning rather than speed. Each of 156 children completed Planned Codes using two different sets of directions. The first set of directions allowed each child to use strategies to complete Planned Codes. The second set of directions allowed the child only to use speed to complete Planned Codes. The results of the study indicated significantly higher scores ( t =11.5, P r =.23; P"
